# 💊 PharmaWatch

PharmaWatch is a medicine stock and expiry monitoring app built with React, Vite, and DHIS2 UI. It helps health facilities manage their inventory by tracking stock levels, expiry dates, and more — all in a clean, responsive dashboard.

### 🌐 Live App
👉 [https://kalbertson85.github.io/pharmawatch/](https://kalbertson85.github.io/pharmawatch/)

---

## ✨ Features

- 📋 Medicine listing with filtering and searching  
- 🔍 Cascading location filters (Country → District → Chiefdom → Facility)  
- ⚠️ Expiry and stock status indicators  
- 🧠 Inline role-based editing for admins  
- 📤 CSV Export functionality  
- 🔐 Audit logging for edits and deletions  
- 📱 Fully responsive (mobile/tablet friendly)  
- 🧩 Modular, component-based architecture  
- 🖼️ DHIS2-compliant UI using TailwindCSS  

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### 1. Clone the repository

**git clone https://github.com/kalbertson85/pharmawatch.git**
**cd pharmawatch**

---
### 2. Install dependencies Clone the repository

**npm install**
This installs all required packages listed in package.json.

### 3. Run the app locally
npm run dev
This starts the development server (usually at http://localhost:5173) where you can view and test the app live.


### Build and Deploy
To build the app for production:
npm run build
*This outputs optimized files to the dist folder.*


To deploy the production build (using gh-pages):
*npm run deploy*
Make sure your GitHub repo is configured correctly before deploying.


Technologies Used
	•	React 18
	•	Vite
	•	DHIS2 UI components
	•	date-fns
	•	TailwindCSS
	•	React Router
	•	Sonner for notifications
	•	And others (see package.json)

